.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-mesh - Discover and chat with models on other nodes over the mesh


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel mesh [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover the models served by OTHER citadel nodes on the AceTeam Network
(the mesh) and route chat requests to them directly, node-to-node.

.PP
Each node publishes its served models at its /status endpoint over the mesh
(served by \fBcitadel work --gateway\fR). \fBcitadel mesh\fR enumerates online peers,
probes each one's /status, and aggregates a fabric-wide model -> node/engine/port
view. Peers that are unreachable (not serving the status endpoint on the mesh)
are skipped gracefully.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for mesh

.PP
\fB--port\fP=8080
	Peer status endpoint port to probe over the mesh


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-mesh-chat(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-mesh-models(1)\fP
